==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tantamount
<hw>Tan"ta*mount`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>tant</ets> so much (L. <ets>tantus</ets>) + E.
<ets>amount</ets>.]</ety> <def>Equivalent in value, signification, or
effect.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A usage nearly <qex>tantamount</qex> to constitutional right.</q>
<rj><qau>Hallam.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The certainty that delay, under these circumstances, was
<qex>tantamount</qex> to ruin.</q> <rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tantamount</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Tantamount
<hw>Tan"ta*mount`</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To be tantamount or
equivalent; to amount.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Jer.
Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tantivy</ent>⟦br⟧
